    "summary": "Endurance, driven, unafraid of improvisation, non-stop learning, a fresh view on what goes on in the business world because I don't origin from it, ability to work and communicate on all levels within a company, always looking for thrills, innovation and fun. Those are my natural qualities which are omnipresent in the performing arts and mix with the characters and situations I encounter in the businessworld. I performed the role of management assistant, executive secretary, office manager, commercial assistant, you name it within a wide variety of businesses: semi-commercial and highly commercial. My goal is not to switch environments constantly but the market directs, especially now. If given a chance I can ground and let a team share and benefit from my working experience and flexibility. I was raised bilingual in Dutch and German and master a foreign language quickly. My English is good and used daily, Spanish is active and alive, French is also active but on a basic communication level. After 9 years in supporting roles for which I didn't receive any training at all, I'm ready to step into a commercial role with budget responsibility.\n\nSpecialties: Dramaturgy: shaping roughly existing ideas into theatre, dance and film scenes; mediator between director and cast on the stage; creative empowerment training for foreign language audiences. Personal qualities other than listed before: quick adaptation, open minded, enthusiastic, imaginative, exploring, playful, analytical, thinking in images, left-handed, musically, works best with sparring partners. I am used to a very busy working week with a freelance theatre business next to my job.",
