                    "description": "My business is theatrical research; discovering dramatic possibilities in situations and texts. I collaborate with director, actors and technicians in creating and generating scenes. 2002 I began my own theatre projects next to keeping a regular job in the business world. Situations I encounter in this challenging mixture, feed my creative thinking. My personal interest lies in stories of migration and survival. Two pillars closely connected, touched and influenced by history. Coming forth from a Dutch-German marriage with family members living in the USA I explore the historical context of my own generation and that of our (great)grandparents in those 3 countries during turbulent times. Next to creating performing art productions I specialise in theatre workshops for foreign language audiences. Personal stories form the base and are moulded into scenes. In particular (young) groups benefit greatly from the educational and healing effect of sharing hidden emotions and creating ways to reflect together on pain, sorrow and sudden displacement.",
                    "title": "Dramaturg/ Trainer",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
